## Description {#details}

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/trace">Trace</a> object represents the records that have been loaded from XRay log files generated by instrumented binaries.

We encapsulate the logic of reading the traces in factory functions that populate the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/trace">Trace</a> object appropriately.

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/trace">Trace</a> objects provide an accessor to an <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xray/xrayfileheader">XRayFileHeader</a> which says more about details of the file from which the XRay trace was loaded from.

Usage:

if (auto TraceOrErr = loadTraceFile(&quot;xray-log.something.xray&quot;)) &#123; auto&amp; T = &#42;TraceOrErr; // T.getFileHeader() will provide information from the trace header. for (const <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xray/xrayrecord">XRayRecord</a> &amp;R : T) &#123; // ... do something with R here. &#125; &#125; else &#123; // Handle the error here. &#125;
